Description: Fix CVE-2020-14061 - Block Oracle AQ JMS connection factory gadget classes
 jackson-databind 2.x before 2.9.10.5 mishandles the interaction between
 serialization gadgets and typing, allowing remote code execution via
 oracle.jms.AQjms* connection factory classes (weblogic/oracle-aqjms gadget).
 .
 Upstream fix (commit 5c8642aeae9c756b438ab7637c90ef3c77966e6e) added the
 5 class names to SubTypeValidator.DEFAULT_NO_DESER_CLASS_NAMES. Backported
 here to BeanDeserializerFactory.DEFAULT_NO_DESER_CLASS_NAMES because
 SubTypeValidator.java was introduced after 2.9.2 (~2.9.10) as part of a
 refactor that extracted the blocklist out of BeanDeserializerFactory.
 The blocklist semantics are equivalent: pure data (5 String literals to a
 static deny-set), no API surface change.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/commit/5c8642aeae9c756b438ab7637c90ef3c77966e6e
Author: Tatu Saloranta <tatu.saloranta@iki.fi>
Bug: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/issues/2698
Last-Update: 2026-06-10

